description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has become available to recruit into the Children and Young Persons Oncology Outreach Nursing Service. (CYPOONS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role development opportunity would start at band 6 nurse specialist level working towards being an autonomous practitioner at band 7 who has accountability for a patient caseload, providing highly specialist nursing skills, knowledge and expertise for CYP (0-24yrs) with cancer and their families across all stages of the illness journey. This service also has an urgent 24/7 on call service to provide essential and responsive nursing resource with the remit of expert symptom management and end of life care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates will have experience in caring for this complex and diverse patient group and knowledge of the specific needs of this specialised service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be supported by an established multi-disciplinary team, within the framework of a dynamic children&#39;s hospital. Please refer to the Job description and Person Specification for all essential and desirable criteria required for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part Tim - 28 hours 12 minutes/week x3 shifts per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
